---
description: Test file rules
globs: "**/*.test.*,**/*.spec.*,**/test_*.py,**/*_test.py,**/*_test.go,**/*_test.rs"
---

- One behavior per test function (Arrange → Act → Assert).
- Use descriptive test names that explain the expected behavior, not the implementation.
- Mock external dependencies (APIs, databases, file systems) — never hit real services in unit tests.
- Cover happy path, edge cases, and error cases for each public function.
- Keep test setup minimal — use fixtures or factories, not complex setUp methods.
- Follow the project test command defined in `CLAUDE.md`.

